## Dependencies & Execution Order

### Phase Dependencies

- **Setup (Phase 1)**: No dependencies - can start immediately
- **Foundational (Phase 2)**: Depends on Setup completion - BLOCKS all user stories
- **User Story 1 (Phase 3)**: Depends on Foundational completion - can proceed independently
- **User Story 4 (Phase 4)**: Depends on Foundational completion - can proceed independently (provides code for US2)
- **User Story 2 (Phase 5)**: Depends on Foundational completion AND User Story 4 completion (references code examples)
- **User Story 3 (Phase 6)**: Depends on Foundational completion AND User Story 2 completion (applies concepts from technical chapters)
- **Synthesis (Phase 7)**: Depends on all previous user stories completion
- **Polish (Phase 8)**: Depends on all content completion (User Stories 1-3 + Chapter 12)

### User Story Dependencies

- **User Story 1 (P1)**: Can start after Foundational (Phase 2) - No dependencies on other stories
- **User Story 4 (P2)**: Can start after Foundational (Phase 2) - No dependencies on other stories (but supports US2)
- **User Story 2 (P2)**: Can start after Foundational (Phase 2) AND User Story 4 (code examples ready) - Depends on US4
- **User Story 3 (P3)**: Can start after User Story 2 completion (applies technical concepts) - Depends on US2

### Within Each User Story

- **User Story 1**: All chapter writing tasks [P] can run in parallel; glossary, exercises, diagrams, and sidebars updates sequential after chapters
- **User Story 4**: All code example creation tasks [P] can run in parallel; tests sequential after code; README and metadata updates sequential
- **User Story 2**: All chapter writing tasks [P] can run in parallel; glossary, exercises, diagrams, and sidebars updates sequential after chapters
- **User Story 3**: All chapter writing tasks [P] can run in parallel; glossary, exercises, diagrams, and sidebars updates sequential after chapters

### Parallel Opportunities

- All Setup tasks (T001-T011) can run in parallel except T001 (Docusaurus init must be first)
- All Foundational tasks (T012-T021) marked [P] can run in parallel
- Within User Story 1: T022, T023, T024 (chapter writing) can run in parallel
- Within User Story 4: T036-T047 (code examples) can run in parallel; T048-T051 (tests) can run in parallel after code is complete
- Within User Story 2: T055-T059 (chapter writing) can run in parallel
- Within User Story 3: T077-T079 (case study writing) can run in parallel
- Polish tasks (T095-T104, T108-T110) marked [P] can run in parallel

